Well of course I get a trip to Boston so V delays the patch until I leave .... &lt;rofl&gt; back now, so here is a brief distillation of what I have found from friends and offline sources:<br>
<br>
Smithing:<br>
<br>
Ornate Chain is working now but some concerns remain with the HQ rings recipe.  The in game book, btw, is on a night stand in MM, but you can view the text offline.<br>
<br>
This is supposed to be a non cultural item. Early data on stats is one ac better than banded on each piece and half a pound lighter on each piece.  Who can wear apears to be same as banded, have not seen an item picture yet, an early report claimed this was not the case.<br>
<br>
Looks: close to banded, no pictures yet. Dyed : appears the answer is NO at this time.  Costs/skills: Cost appears to be higher than plate, trivial appears to be lower.<br>
<br>
<br>
FS Plate updates:<br>
<br>
   An early suggestion that trivials had changed has ben rebutted by some early data.  Dyed FS will now give an actual name change to the item, so you will now know what you are buying and selling without putting it on first. (Nice for those who can't wear the stuff)<br>
<br>
Other smithing:<br>
<br>
Two new items were added as cultural, special cultural sewing kits for wood elves and hobbits.  Alas, the hq metal bits appear to be bugged snuffing all attempts to make this stuff until a further update/bug fix. &lt;f&gt;<br>
<br>
Cultural Tailoring:<br>
<br>
Wood elves and Halflings each have new magic studded and reinforced armour items.  Note the problem above.<br>
<br>
Wood Elves need a gound spawn bark (7 points locced in Kith and another forest) for their temper, Halflings need a groundspawn Acorn (Misty only - 12 locs found so far.<br>
<br>
<br>
The pelt/fur required atleast for halflings is brute from Kunark and HQ brute also from Kunark, so it appears you must now have Kunark for these cultural tradeskills.  I believe this is a first in tradeskills and just a real dissapointment to a halfling player like myself. &lt;bf&gt;<br>
<br>
So save me some brute pelts and HQ brute pelts please boys and girls and note the weight is 5 each non stack. &lt;lol&gt;<br>
<br>
A new shaman item was added with wide ranging uses.<br>
<br>
recipe is one grizzly pelt and one silk cord, combines to form a ten slot container that holds small items only and weighs 3/10 of a pound.  Shaman can combine 5 or ten potions at a time to make a 5 or 10 charges potion.  A nice effect.  Many predict these will be in demand from casters monks and the like to hold patterns and such as a cheap alternative to ten slot back packs.  There is still that nasty combine button to watch out for &lt;g&gt;<br>
<br>
Good tradeskilling and SAVE ME SOME BRUTE PELTS !<br>
